4 But there are not wanting opinions which bear the other way, of which we willsadduce some. The determination of this question depends on this, whether deceit in its kind be always a bad thing: if so, we are not to do evil that good may come: or whether it be a thing of that kind which is not universally bad by its nature, but which may happen to be good.
